Quote:  b. kick like a run cow The depth [of furrow of a swing plough] was graduated by the bridle adjustment but was corrected in uneven ground by leverage from the long handles, or stilts as they were called.  if the the share struck anything these [swing ploughs] had a kick like a run cow. it is said that a good man could land on his feet six yards in front of the horses ...
